Use OrderedDict for python 3.5 compatibility

python 3.5 uses unordered dicts, so the long NWIS.__repr__() can vary the content order, causing my tests to fail.
This explicitly makes NWIS.meta an ordered dict, keeping the order set by the USGS's json response.

I also altered some tests that were checking with assertIs to check type, instead of assertIsInstance, which allows for subclasses of dict.

Add .json.gz file extension to filenames w/o extensions

Filenames that are only one 'part' (have no "." separators) will have
'json.gz' added to their filename. This caused two tests to fail because
they were expected to call 'parquet' even though they had no file
extensions. So I added .parquet to them to make them pass. Now I need to
create a filter for parquet extensions and for gzip extensions.
